<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-17T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="750" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/655: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-17T15:00:00+09:00">May 17, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 17—6:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>316. Our 314, May 17, 11 a.m.<note n="91" xml:id="d750fn91">Not printed;
                                for memorandum of May 17 recording oral representations to the
                                Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_743"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 743</ref>.</note> We have now fully registered
                            our position. I am reluctantly of the opinion that further
                            representations along these lines by us at present would accomplish no
                            constructive results.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>